ComicInfo.Summary: First of a special three-issue story arc celebrating female comic book characters- Superbabes!! First in a great, all-new Femforce lead story, journey into the past to experience a never-before-told tale out of the case files of the Femforce of the 1950's, in "0ut of the Past". See Miss Victory, She-Cat, Blue Bulleteer, Rio Rita and (seen in action with The Femforce for the FIRST TIME since 1980's Femzine #1!!!) The Blonde Bomber face off against the awesome mystical power of Rathschilde, the weird, giant sorceress. Where does she get her strange powers, and what is her connection to Rio Rita's past? Written by Mark and Stephanie Heike, with art by the awesome duo of Gianluca Cerutelli and Jeff Austin. Then, in the present, Nightveil faces an unseen enemy in the limbo void in "Machinations", written and inked by Mark Heike, and penciled by returning AC favorite Chris Allen. An actual vintage Golden Age Rio Rita adventure rounds out the FF fun, straight out of the pages of Fiction House's Fight comics; then it's the special Superbabes guest-story by long-time comics and animation great, Will Meugniot- Mary America! Set in the warn-torn skies of 1940's Germany, Mary and her ally Dr. Allset take off in there amazing wave-plane to take on the Axis fury of- the Silver Salamander! Wild, way-out pulp-style "good girl art" super-heroics starring this brand-new, never-before-seen heroine created, written and drawn by the amazing Mr. Meugniot!! Plus- the conclusion of Jason Greenfields's "Worlds of Justice" prose story. Black and white with color covers, 44 pages, 6" X 10" size.
ComicInfo.Title: Out of the Past
